Unfortunately, respect for the flag and properly displaying it seems to be forgotten.
Local McDonalds has eight (I counted them) on their roof.
Two Car Dealerships have massive American Flags flying over their establishments.
While I don't object to this it is kind of distracting when they are across the street from one another.
How many flag type clothing garments (jackets, hats, purses, shirts, pants, etc have you seen).
How many US Flags have you seen with motorycycles, chevy, ford, and other emblems superimposed on them.
I have on 3x5 foot flag on my flag pole in my front yard.
A light automatically shines up on it when the sun goes down and stays on all night.
